  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Canon
    An implementation based on the canon algorithm [Weininger, David and Weininger, Arthur and Weininger, Joseph L., SMILES 2. Algorithm for Generation of Unique SMILES Notation, Journal of Chemical Information and Computer Sciences, 1989, 29:97-101].
    CanonicalLabeler Deprecated
    this labeller uses slow data structures and has been replaced - Canon
    ConjugatedPiSystemsDetector  
    EquivalentClassPartitioner
    An algorithm for topological symmetry.
    GIMatrix
    This class is intended to provide the user an efficient way of implementing matrix of double number and using normal operations (linear operations, addition, substraction, multiplication, inversion, concatenation) on them.
    HuLuIndexTool
    Collection of methods for the calculation of topological indices of a molecular graph.
    InChINumbersTools
    Tool for calculating atom numbers using the InChI algorithm.
    MorganNumbersTools
    Compute the extended connectivity values (Morgan Numbers) [Morgan, H.L., The Generation of a Unique Machine Description for Chemical Structures - A Technique Developed at Chemical Abstracts Service., J.Chem.Doc., 1965, 5:107-113].
